        The function ftrace_make_nop() is used to replace the machine code at specified
        location to "nop" instruction.
        macro MCOUNT_ADDR is defined in <arch/x86/include/asm/ftrace.h>,will be expanded
        to "((unsigned long)(__fentry__))".
        symbol "__fentry__" associated with a function which is defined in the
        <arch/x86/kernel/ftrace_64.S>,it does nothing.
        when system booting,the functions' "call __fentry__" will be replaced to "nop"
        instruction through ftrace_modify_code_direct(),ftrace_make_nop() call to this
        function when the passed @address is equal to MCOUNT_ADDR,the direct modification
        will replace the instruction to "nop".
        this also affects module loading,when a module is loaded,its "call __fentry__"
        also be replaced to "nop".
        This behavior happens either running before SMP or before the code will ever
        be executed(module load).
        This replacement only happens once.after ftrace is enabled,the "nop" is switch
        to ftrace caller;when we unregister a @ops,its flag would be set to DELETED,and
        unlink from global ops list,its trampoline will be freed through execmem_free().
        if the function is no other ftrace_ops is associated with now,the call to
        ftrace caller will be replaced to "nop" instruction,it never become
        "call __fentry__" again. /* if we disbale ftrace through sysctl,the records
                                  * in ftrace pages,their @ip -- mcount call-site
                                  * all will be replaced to "nop"
                                  */
        ! x86 overrides ftrace_replace_code(),thus the function ftrace_make_nop() only
          be called during initialization,and the valid control path is modify
          MCOUNT_ADDR to "nop".
          after system started,any make nop work are hands over to smp_text_poke_batch_add(),
          which is called by x86 ftrace_replace_code() to batch pokings,before return
          from ftrace_replace_code(),smp_text_poke_batch_finish() is called to appiles
          these changes.
          the initial records in ftrace pages are created by ftrace_process_locs(),
          for the addresses in "__start_mcount_loc" to "__stop_mcount_loc",a record
          is created that associated with the address.
          # x86 has no ftrace_dyn_arch_init(),the default just return 0 without do nothing.
            this function and ftrace_process_locs() are called in ftrace_init(),and
            ftrace_init() is called in start_kernel().
            at the end of ftrace_process_locs(),function ftrace_update_code() is called,
            if architecture requires mcount call-site init nop,then ftrace_make_nop()
            is called with MCOUNT_ADDR for each ftrace records,so the function's
            "call __fentry__" is replaced to "nop" instruction.

