          bpf-helpers(7).

        eBPF instruction set :
          general registers in eBPF >
                  r0 => return value or exit code
            r1 -- r5 => arguments for function calls
            r6 -- r9 => callee saved registers that function calls will preserve
                 r10 => read-only frame pointer to access stack

            ! when a eBPF program start running,the bpf_reg0 contains a pointer to
              context(void *),this context can be used for other eBPF helpers
              such bpf_tail_call().
            ! The rN register naming,is not means to the general purpose registers
              that coming with CPU architecture,such R8, R9, etc.
              They only meaningful in eBPF.

          instruction encoding >
            eBPF uses 64-bit instructions
                    32           16        4          4          8
                    immediate    offset    src-reg    dst-reg    opcode

                    MSB                                          LSB
        
                    not all fields are used by instructions,for the unused fields,
                    need to be zero out.

          instruction classes >
            BPF_LD        0x00        non-standard load operations
            BPF_LDX       0x01        load into reg operations
            BPF_ST        0x02        store from imm operations
            BPF_STX       0x03        store from reg operations
            BPF_ALU       0x04        32-bit arithmetic operations
            BPF_JMP       0x05        64-btt jump
            BPF_JMP32     0x06        32-bit jump
            BPF_ALU64     0x07        64-bit arithmetic operations

          arithmetic and jump >
            the encoding is
                    4         1      3
                    opcode    src    ins-class

                    MSB              LSB

            source operand mode
              BPF_K    0x00        use 32-bit imm as src operand
              BPF_X    0x08        use .src_reg reg as src operand

            arithmetic instructions
              BPF_ADD        0x00        dst += src
              BPF_SUB        0x10        dst -= src
              BPF_MUL        0x20        dst *= src
              BPF_DIV        0x30        dst /= src
              BPF_OR         0x40        dst |= src
              BPF_AND        0x50        dst &= src
              BPF_LSH        0x60        dst <<= src
              BPF_RSH        0x70        dst >>= src
              BPF_NEG        0x80        dst = ~src
              BPF_MOD        0x90        dst %= src
              BPF_XOR        0xa0        dst ^= src
              BPF_MOV        0xb0        dst = src
              BPF_ARSH       0xc0        signed extending shift right
              BPF_END        0xd0        endianness converstion

            jump instructions
              BPF_JA         0x00        pc += off
              BPF_JEQ        0x10        pc += off if dst == src
              BPF_JGT        0x20        pc += off if dst > src
              BPF_JGE        0x30        pc += off if dst >= src
              BPF_JSET       0x40        pc += off if dst & src
              BPF_JNE        0x50        pc += off if dst != src
              BPF_JSGT       0x60        pc += off if dst > src
              BPF_JSGE       0x70        pc += off if dst >= src
              BPF_CALL       0x80        function call
              BPF_EXIT       0x90        function / program return
              BPF_JLT        0xa0        pc += off if dst < src
              BPF_JLE        0xb0        pc += off if dst <= src
              BPF_JSLT       0xc0        pc += off if dst < src
              BPF_JSLE       0xd0        pf += off if dst <= src

              ! for conditional jump, 'S' means signed, no 'S' means unsigned .
              ! BPF_JA and BPF_JMP requires instruction class BPF_JMP.
              ! @pc points to next instruction.

          load and store >
            instruction encoding
                    3       2       3
                    mode    size    insn-class

            size modifier
              BPF_W        0x00        word(4 bytes)
              BPF_H        0x08        half word
              BPF_B        0x10        byte
              BPF_DW       0x18        double word

            mode modifier
              BPF_IMM        0x00        for 64-bit mov
              BPF_ABS        0x20        legacy BPF packet access
              BPF_IND        0x40        legacy BPF packet access
              BPF_MEM        0x60        all normal load and store ops
              BPF_ATOMIC     0xc0        atomic

              ! BPF_MEM means treat the target as a pointer points to the data has
                length @size,and derefer the pointer.

            the .imm field can be used for extra encoding that support
            atomic operations :
              .imm = arithmetic opcode
              .code = BPF_ATOMIC | BPF_W | BPF_STX

              => lock xadd *(u32 *)(.dst_reg + off16) @arithmetic-op .src_reg
            
            ! supported atomic operations
                BPF_ADD
                BPF_AND
                BPF_OR
                BPF_XOR
                
              special atomic operations
                BPF_XCHG        exchange .src_reg with *(.dst_reg + off)

                BPF_CMPXCHG     if *(.dst_reg + off) == R0
                                        exchange *(.dst_reg + off) with .src_reg
                                oldv = zero-extend(old *(.dst_reg + off))
                                load @oldv into R0
                
              ! 1 and 2 byte atomic operations are not supported.

            16-byte instruction
              the load operation that instruction is
                      BPF_LD | BPF_DW | BPF_IMM
              consists of two consecutive struct bpf_insn 8-byte blocks.
              it loads 64-bit immediate value into .dst_reg

              when we using the operation,we must fill the first block,and
              the first block's .imm stores the lower 32bits of data;the
              second block should zero-outted,execpt its .imm stores the
              upper 32bits of data.
                /* 16-byte instruction start */
                prog_insns[0] = bpf_insn object contains 16 byte instruction
                prog_insns[1] = {0}
                prog_insns[1].imm = upper 32 bits of data
                /* 16-byte instruction end */

              ! when we want to pass a string pointer to print helper like
                bpf_trace_printk(),we can not just pass the pointer of
                string to BPF_REG_1.
                we use 16-byte instruction / BPF_MOV to load pointer into
                r1,verifier will throws "expected=fp" exception,because
                it wants us to store into r1 a stack frame pointer rather
                then pointer to the string.
                # when we move a value into register,BPF_MOV flags the
                  state of reg as SCALE_VALUE.
                  when load immediate value through BPF_LD,verifier assumes
                  the value is an unspecifiable Scalar or Pointer.
                  when we BPF_MOV BPF_REG_10(stack pointer) to another register,
                  the target register should be flaged Stack Frame Pointer.
                  bpf_trace_printk() wants first parameter is stack frame
                  pointer,that is why eBPF throws "type=inv, expected=fp".
                suppose we fix the previous problem by store the pointer
                at stack position "r10 - 8"(high addr to low addr),and
                store into r1 the result of "r10 - 8" -- stack frame pointer,
                this will cause nested pointer -- pointer to pointer,we can
                address the string through "*(*r1)",this is a not allowed
                in a lot of helpers.
                # error "invalid stack type"
                    1> uninitialized bytes
                    2> misaligned pointers
                    3> reading outside boundaries
                to fix this problem,we use BPF_MOV and BPF_STX to store the
                string directly on stack,and then we store into r1 the stack
                pointer,this is OK.
                or,we update map at first,and invoke bfp_map_lookup_elem() in
                the bpf program,if that function succeed to find the string,
                in BPF_REG_0,the stack frame pointer to that string is stored.
                next,we BPF_MOV BPF_REG_0 into BPF_REG1,that is OK.

              ! eBPF only supports 64 bits pointer arithmetic,the 32-bit pointer
                arithmetic is prohibited.

              ! special usage of 16-byte operation
                  BPF_PSEUDO_MAP_FD == 1

                  {
                          .code = BPF_IMM | BPF_DW | BPF_LD,
                          .src_reg = BPF_PSEUDO_MAP_FD,
                          .dst_reg = BPF_REG_1,
                          .off = 0
                          .imm = @map_fd,
                  },
                  {
                          .code = 0,
                  },

                this bpf bytecode sequence can help us convert the bpf map fd to
                the map pointer that is required by bpf_map_lookup_elem().
                in userspace,we usually only has a map fd returned by bpf(),
                through the 16-byte load operation,we can get the corresponding
                map pointer that points to the map entity in Kernel Mode,because
                the bytecode only be executed in Kernel Mode BPF virtual machine,
                thus userspace can not know the exact address of that map entity.

                we can combine bpf_map_lookup_elem() and printing helpers that
                printing usually requires the first parameter is a stack pointer
                to the fmt,if we succeed to find out the element in map,we can
                move content of BPF_REG_0 into BPF_REG_1 to get the stack pointer
                indirectly,without need to puts fmt on stack.
                but for do this,we must update the map at first.

            packet access instructions
              eBPF has two non-generic instructions
                      BPF_ABS | @size | BPF_LD
                      BPF_IND | @size | BPF_LD
              these two instructions are used to access packet data.
              they can only be used when interpreter context is a pointer
              to struct sk_buff object,and have seven implicit operands.
              R6 is an implicit input hat must contain pointer to sk_buff.
              R0 is an implicit output which contains the data fetched
              from the packet.
              R1 -- R5 are scratch registers and must not be used to store
              the data across BPF_ABS | BPF_LD and BPF_IND | BPF_LD.
              .src_reg and .imm are explicit inputs to these instructions.

              ! when an eBPF program try to access packet data beyond the
                boundary,the interpreter will abort the execution of the program.

              e.g.
                BPF_IND | BPF_W | BPF_LD
                => R0 = ntohl(*(u32 *)(((struct sk_buff *)R6)->data + .src_reg + .imm))
                
                R1 -- R5 are clobbered

BPF in kernel :
        the system call bpf() is defined in <kernel/bpf/syscall.c>.

        <kernel/bpf/syscall.c>
          /**
           * sys_bpf - the system call service routine for bpf()
           * @cmd:     BPF command
           * @uattr:   BPF attritbue union
           * @size:    attribute union size
           * return:   0 OR error code
           * # this function just a wrapper to __sys_bpf().
           *   @uattr will be converted by USER_BPFPTR() before pass to
           *   __sys_bpf().
           * # "static inline bpfptr_t USER_BPFPTR(void __user *p);" is
           *   defined in <linux/bpfptr.h>,it returns an object is type of
           *   bpfptr_t,the member @user is set to @p.
           *   bpfptr_t is a type alias of type sockptr_t.
           */
          SYSCALL_DEFINE3(bpf, int, cmd, union bpf_attr __user *, uattr,
                          unsigned int size);
          => asmlinkage long sys_bpf(int cmd, union bpf_attr __user *uattr,
                                     unsigned int size);

          /**
           * __sys_bpf - the BPF command dispatcher
           * @cmd:       command
           * @uattr:     attribute
           * @size:      size of attribute from User Mode
           * return:     0 OR error code
           */
          static int __sys_bpf(enum bpf_cmd cmd, bpfptr_t uattr, unsigned int size);

          description for __sys_bpf() :
            at the beginning,this routine invoke bpf_check_uarg_tail_zero() on @uattr,
            with its size and the @size of User Mode attribute.
            /**
             * attribute @size cant larger than PAGE_SIZE,otherwise -E2BIG.
             * for attribute from User Mode(@uattr.is_kernel set to false),
             * invoke check_zeroed_user(),it is defined in <lib/usercopy.c>.
             * the routine checks whether the memory space determined by a
             * given start position and a size value is all zeroed out.
             * in bpf_check_uarg_tail_zero(),we expect the memory start
             * from "@uattr.user + sizeof(bpfptr_t)" with size "@size - sizeof(bpfptr_t)"
             * is all zero filled.
             */
            next,take the minimal value between @size and sizeof(union bpf_attr),then
            we copy attribute from User Mode in local object @attr with the size.
            invoke security_bpf(),pass it @cmd, &@attr, the minimal size, @uattr.is_kernel,
            to does security checking(LSM),if security test failed,we return the error code.
            invoke different helper functions depends on @command.
            /* there is a lot of commands available,we would not describe all things. */
            for BPF_MAP_CREATE
              map_create() is called,pass &@attr, @uattr.
            for BPF_MAP_LOOKUP_ELEM
              map_lookup_elem() is called,pass &@attr.
            for BPF_MAP_UPDATE_ELEM
              map_update_elem() is called,pass &@attr, @uattr.
            for BPF_PROG_LOAD
              bpf_prog_load() is called,pass &@attr, @uattr,the minimal size.
            return value of this __sys_bpf() depends on the called helper.

          /**
           * CHECK_ATTR - this macro is used to check unused fields of 'union bpf_attr' are
           *              zero.
           * @CMD:        current command relative to the @attr
           * return:      true  => Bad
           *              false => OK
           * # in the definition,name @attr is used,thus the scope called this macro must
           *   has such object matches the name.
           */
          #define CHECK_ATTR(CMD)

          /**
           * map_create - handler for command BPF_MAP_CREATE.
           * @attr:       BPF attr,local object but data copied from User Mode.
           * @uattr:      bpfptr_t object.
           * return:      0 OR error code
           */
          static int map_create(union bpf_attr *attr, bpfptr_t uattr);

          description for map_create() :
            first,get NUMA node number of the @attr through bpf_map_attr_numa_node().
            if @attr->map_flags enabled BPF_F_NUMA_NODE,then we use @attr->numa_node.
            otherwise,the node is NUMA_NO_NODE.
            check @attr through CHECK_ATTR(),if unused fields are not zeroed,returns
            -EINVAL.
            extrace value of BPF_F_TOKEN_FD in @attr->map_flags,and disable the flag.
            if @attr->btf_vmlinux_value_type_id is TRUE,there are three conditions
            must not be satisfied,otherwise,returns -EINVAL.
              cond 1 => @attr->map_type cant be BPF_MAP_TYPE_STRUCT_OPS
              cond 2 => @attr->btf_key_type_id must be zero
              cond 3 => @attr->btf_value_type_id must be zero
            if no @btf_vmlinux_value_type_id,we just requires @btf_key_type_id is zero
            OR @btf_value_type_id is not zero.
            proceeding to check map type,if it is not BFP_MAP_TYPE_BLOOM_FILTER AND it
            is not BPF_MAP_TYPE_ARENA but @attr->map_extra is not zero,that will be
            invalid;only these two types can let @map_extra to _zero_.
            next,invoke bpf_get_file_flag() on @map_flags to get file flag,
              BPF_F_RDONLY => O_RDONLY
              BPF_F_WRONLY => O_WRONLY
              no both two specified => O_RDWR
              /* both are specified in flags is invalid case */
            if NUMA node is not NUMA_NO_NODE,the node number must be less than maximum
            number value and which must be online now.
            @map_type can in valid range of map types.
            convert @map_type to array idx through array_index_nospec(),on array @bpf_map_types.
            use the idx to retrieves bpf_map_ops object in @bpf_map_types[],if no such
            ops is registered,returns -EINVAL.
            if @ops requires check before allocate memory(@map_alloc_check() method is not NULL),
            must does checking at first,failed to pass test then give up to this creation.
            if @attr->map_ifindex is not _zero_,we use @bpf_map_offload_ops rather than the @ops
            from @bpf_map_types[].
            for either @ops,@map_mem_usage() method must be defined.
            now,check token flag,if token flag is set before,we get token through function
            bpf_token_get_from_fd(),pass it @attr->map_token_fd.
            if the token does not allow BPF_MAP_CREATE command OR does not allow current @map_type,
            we put the token and set @token to NULL./* ignore the token,we'll use system-wide
                                                     * capabilities checks later
                                                     */
            check if @sysctl_unprivileged_bpf_disabled AND bpf_token_capable() on @token
            disallowed CAP_BPF,we goto label "put_token",give up creation.
            /* system-wide capability allowed CAP_BPF or we are root user,return TRUE */
            for a lot of map types,there is no additional testing,but for BFP_MAP_TYPE_XSKMAP,
            we need CAP_NET_ADMIN,for BPF_MAP_TYPE_INSN_ARRAY,we need CAP_BPF.
            now we can allocate map through @ops->map_alloc(),pass it @attr,if succeed,it will
            create an object is type of struct bpf_map and returns the object's address.
            use @ops and @map_type(get from @bpf_map_types,idx) set the @map.
            if we specified @map_name in @attr,copy the named into @map.
            disable preemption,invoke gen_cookie_next() on @bpf_map_cookie to create cookie
            for this new @map,set its @cookie member,enable preemption.
            set @map->refcnt to 1,@map->usercnt to 1,init @map->freeze_mutex.
            spinlock acquire @map->owner_lock.
            check,if @btf_key_type id is not zero OR @btf_value_type_id is not zero OR
            @btf_vmlinux_value_type_id is not zero,then we need invoke btf_get_by_fd()
            on @attr->btf_fd to get a btf descriptor,use @btf to set @map->btf;use @attr's
            @btf_key_type_id,@btf_value_type_id,@btf_vmlinux_value_type_id to setup
            corresponding members in @map.
            /* @btf can not be kernel space btf,and if @attr->btf_value_type_id is not zero,
             * we need to call map_check_btf(),pass it @map, @token, @btf, @btf_key_type_id,
             * @btf_value_type_id.
             */
            check @attr->excl_prog_hash,if it is true,we need to make_bpfptr() from @attr's
            @excl_prog_hash,and copy the hash into @map->excl_prog_sha.
            if @excl_prog_hash is not true but @attr->excl_prog_hash_size is not zero,returns
            -EINVAL.
            invoke security_bpf_map_create(),does security test(Linux Security Module).
            allocate 'id' for @map through bpf_map_alloc_id().
            /* this calling will publish this @map into userspace */
            invoke bpf_map_save_memcg() on @map to set memory cgroup info into @map->objcg,
            if @memcg_bpf_enabled() returned ture. /* cgroup info get through
                                                    * get_obj_cgroup_from_current(),that is
                                                    * object cgroup of current task.
                                                    */
            put token,allocate new file descriptor based on file flags(extraced before) for
            @map. /* if failed,invoke bpf_map_put_with_uref() on @map to decrease @usercnt,
                   * @refcnt,free 'id' if necessary -- @refcnt becomes zero.
                   * free @map.
                   * ! the bpf_map descriptor will be stored into fd's private data.
                   */
            finally,return the result to caller.

            /* normal error return path */
            "free_map_sec":
              invoke security_bpf_map_free() to free @map->security,reset to
              NULL.
            "free_map":
              call bpf_map_free() to free @map.
            "put_token":
              call bpf_token_put() on @token.
              return error code.

          /**
           * map_lookup_elem - hander for command BPF_MAP_LOOKUP_ELEM.
           * @attr:            in kernel space BPF attribute descriptor
           * return:           0 OR error code
           * # this routine will does
           *     1> CHECK_ATTR()
           *     2> use @attr->map_fd get bpf_map descriptor,need FMOD_CAN_READ
           *     3> bpf_map_check_op_flags() on @map,@attr->flags,allowed flags is
           *        BPF_F_LOCK -- other flags cause -EINVAL
           *        # if has such flags,@map->record the btf record must has field
           *          BPF_SPIN_LOCK.
           *     4> copy key from @attr,size is @map->key_size
           *     5> get @map->value_size,use the size allocate GFP_USER memory as
           *        buffer
           *     6> for BPF_MAP_TYPE_BLOOM_FILTER,copy @attr->value into value buffer,
           *        and then invoke bpf_map_copy_value() to copy the real value
           *        into value buffer,through @map->ops->map_peek_elem().
           *        # if @map is offloaded map,the work will hands over to 
           *          bpf_map_offload_lookup_elem.
           *        # for this map BPF_MAP_TYPE_BLOOM_FILTER,we just goto label "free_value"
           *          at end of this branch.does not go into 7>
           *     7> invoke bpf_map_copy_value(),invoke copy_to_user() to copy value in
           *        value buffer to @attr->value.
           *     "free_value":
           *       kvfree() value buffer
           *     "free_key":
           *       kvfree() copied key,return result
           */
          static int map_lookup_elem(union bpf_attr *attr);

          /**
           * map_update_elem - handler for command BPF_PROG_LOAD
           * @attr:            in kernel space BPF attribute descriptor
           * @uattr:           bpfptr_t constructed from userspace attribute
           * return:           0 OR error code
           * # this routine similar to map_lookup_elem(),but it copy value from
           *   userspace,and insert it into the map,requires FMODE_CAN_WRITE.
           *   the disallow all flags in bpf_map,otherwise -EINVAL.
           *   # check operation flags
           *   duplicates value into kernel space,and invoke the helper
           *   bpf_map_update_value().(similar to bpf_map_copy_value())
           *   if succeed,we call to maybe_wait_bpf_programs() to RCU sync,
           *   for the map type is BPF_MAP_TYPE_HASH_OF_MAPS OR
           *   BPF_MAP_TYPE_ARRAY_OF_MAPS.
           *   finally,release allocated memory,and return result.
           */
          static int map_update_elem(union bpf_attr *attr, bpfptr_t uattr)

          /**
           * bpf_prog_load - handler for command BPF_PROG_LOAD
           * @attr:          in kernel space attribute descriptor
           * @uattr:         bpfptr_t object constructed from userspace attribute
           * @uattr_size:    size of @uattr
           * return:         0 OR error code
           */
          static int bpf_prog_load(union bpf_attr *attr, bpfptr_t uattr, u32 uattr_size);

          description for bpf_prog_load() :
            the first work still is CHECK_ATTR().
            @attr->prog_flags is restricted to one of the following
              BPF_F_STRICT_ALIGNMENT
              BPF_F_TEST_STATE_FREQ
              BPF_F_SLEEPABLE
              BPF_F_TEST_RND_HI32
              BPF_F_XDP_HAS_FRAGS
              BPF_F_XDP_DEV_BOUND_ONLY
              BPF_F_TEST_REG_INVARIANTS
              BPF_F_TOKEN_FD
            some prog type needs the expected attach type,function
            bpf_prog_load_fixup_attach_type() is used to adjust expected type for
            BPF_PROG_TYPE_CGROUP_SOCK and BPF_PROG_TYPE_SK_REUSEPORT,if current
            prog type is one of those two,and @expected_attach_type of @attr is
            0,set to BPF_CGROUP_INET_SOCK_CREATE and BPF_SK_REUSEPORT_SELECT,
            respectively.
            if BPF_F_TOKEN_FD is enabled in flags,we get the token,the token
            must allows BPF_PROG_LOAD command,otherwise,we use the system-wide
            capabilities checking.(like the action in map_create())
            the system-wide capability must has CAP_BPF,or we are root user.
            /* we can load the program,even @syscal_unprivileged_bpf_disabled,
             * if we have CAP_BPF.
             */
            if no CONFIG_HAVE_EFFICIENT_UNALIGNED_ACCESS AND BPF_F_ANY_ALIGNMENT
            is set in flags AND we have not CAP_BPF,just give up the loading.
            @attr->insn_cnt is _zero_ OR exceeded the maximum value of insns,
            goto "put_token" label,error code is -E2BIG.
            for prog type is neither BPF_PROG_TYPE_SOCKET_FILTER,nor is
            BPF_PROG_TYPE_CGROUP_SKB,we must have CAP_BPF,otherwise give up.
            if current prog type is net admin prog type AND
              /* BPF_PROG_TYPE_CGROUP_SKB and BPF_PROG_TYPE_SK_REUSEPORT
               * #^always unpriv             #^equivalent to SOCKET_FILTER,
               *                               need CAP_BPF only
               * are not net admin prog type
               */
            token has no CAP_NET_ADMIN,give up and goto label "put_token",
            error code is -EPERM.
            else if current type is perfmon prog type but token has no
            CAP_PERFMON,also goto "put_token".
            /* KPROBE, TRACEPOINT, PERF_EVENT, RAW_TRACEPOINT,
             * RAW_TRACEPOINT_WRITABLE, TRACING, LSM, STRUCT_OPS, EXT
             * are perfmon prog type
             */
            test @attr->attach_prog_fd,if this eBPF program wants to attach
            to another program,we need to get dst_prog through @attach_prog_fd,
            if failed to get the program,we use @attr->attach_btf_obj_fd to
            get btf descriptor of that program,both are failed then give up
            this loading. /**
                           * structure btf is defined in
                           *   <kernel/bpf/preload/iterators/iterators_bpf.c>
                           * which contains three members
                           *   const char *strings;
                           *   struct btf_type **types; # contains __u32 @name_off
                           *   struct btf_header hdr;   # contains __u32 @str_len
                           */
            else if no @attach_prog_fd,but has @attr->attach_btf_id,then
            we get the btf descriptor through bpf_get_btf_vmlinux(),failed then
            give up.
            next to check whether we are able to attach to the program,if condition
            is not satisfied,release the bpf_prog descriptor/btf descriptor of that 
            program,and give up loading.
            we ready to allocate new prog descriptor(struct bpf_prog) for the being
            load program through bpf_prog_alloc(),gfp flag is GFP_USER,size is
            computed by bpf_prog_size() based on @attr->insn_cnt.
            setup the fields of the new descriptor,@expected_attach_type,@sleepable,etc.
            copy the instructions in userspace attribute's @insns member into the
            new prog descriptor's @insns member.
            copy license,then check license,because eBPF program hard requires "GPL"
            license.
            if @attr->signature is not zero,invoke bpf_prog_verify_signature() to
            the new prog descriptor,this will verify whether the program constructed
            by a reliable user.
            set @prog->orig_prog to NULL(has no tail call now),and set @prog->jited to 0.
            set @prog->aux->refcnt to 1.if @prog->aux is device bound,invoke
            bpf_prog_dev_bound_init() on @prog with @attr. /* device binding */
            if prog type is BPF_PROG_TYPE_EXT AND @dst_prog is not NULL AND
            @dst_prog is device bound,we invoke bpf_prog_dev_bound_inherit() to let
            @prog derives device bound from this @dst_prog.
            if type is BPF_PROG_TYPE_TRACING AND @dst_prog is not NULL AND @dst_prog's
            type is BPF_PROG_TYPE_TRACING,set @prog->aux->attach_tracing_prog to true.
            try find_prog_type() on @prog with the type,SOCKET_FILTER or TRACING_FILTER,
            the idx of current type into @bpf_prog_types will stored in @prog->type,
            and @ops for this type must been defined.
            set @prog->aux->load_time to the current time since system booted.
            copy @attr->prog_name into @prog->aux->name.
            /* the above goto label "free_prog" or goto "put_token" if failed */

            does LSM testing on @prog. /* goto "free_prog_sec" if failed */

            /* [[ goto label "free_used_maps" if failed */
            call to bpf_check() on @prog,this function will run eBPF verifier on this
            @prog to see whether the instructions of this program is "good"(syntax correct,
            no security violate,etc).
            invoke bpf_prog_select_runtime() on @prog,this function is defined in
            <kernel/bpf/core.c>,which select exec runtime for this eBPF program.
            it tries to JIT this program,if JIT is not available,use interpreter,
            the BFP program will be executed via bpf_prog_run() function.
            invoke bpf_prog_mark_insn_arrays_ready() on @prog.
            /**
             * it processes a for-loop,stop condition is @prog->aux->used_map_cnt
             * is beyonded by iterator.
             * for each prog->aux->used_maps[i],if the map type is BPF_MAP_TYPE_INSN_ARRAY,
             * invoke bpf_insn_array_read() on the map.
             */
            invoke bpf_prog_alloc_id() on @prog,give it an 'id',this will publishes it
            to userspace.
            /* goto label "free_used_maps" if failed ]] */

            invoke bpf_prog_kallsyms_add(),to add this @prog in kallsyms table.
            feed a perf bpf even PERF_BPF_EVENT_PROG_LOAD.
            invoe bpf_audit_prog() on @prog,second parameter is BPF_AUDIT_LOAD,we audit
            this loading.
            invoke bpf_prog_new_fd() to create a new fd for this program.
            finally,return result.

            /* error handing */
            "free_used_maps":
              __bpf_prog_put_noref(),pass it @prog, @prog->aux->real_func_cnt.
              return error code.

            "free_prog_sec":
              security_bpf_prog_free() on @prog.
            "free_prog":
              free_uid() on @prog->aux->user,btf_put() is has any attached btf,
              bpf_prog_free() on @prog to release it.
            "put_token":
              bpf_token_put(),and return error code.

          !! eBPF PROGRAM IS NOT EXECUTED RIGHT AFTER IT BEEN LOADED,BUT RELATED TO
             THE WHAT THE TYPE IT IS.
             FOR EXAMPLE,IF THE PROGRAM IS 'TRACEPOINT',THEN IT WILL BE CALLED WHEN
             KERNEL CONTROL PATH TOUCHED THE CORRESPONDING TRACEPOINT,ON THAT PATH,
             SUCH eBPF PROGRAM USUALLY IS CALLED BY trace_call_bpf().
